      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "OLYMPIA, Oct. Ion the\ngrounds that their time in the OPP\ntion had expired, the supreme court\nhas reversed the decision of the\nsuperior court of Spokane county\nand ruled that the Spokane, Port\nland & Seattle railroad will now\nhave to secure by new arrange\nments right of way through the\nland of l. j. Ballenger and wife\nnear Cheney. Ballenger had given\nthe road an option for six months\non his land; the company failed to\nbuy In that time and later COM\nPEELED the defendant to execute a\ndeed."
